@startuml
title Viaverse Category / Taxonomy / Dynamic Environment — Component Diagram

component "KMP / Next.js Client\ncategory picker\nfilters\nrequest forms" as Client
component "Admin UI\ntaxonomy editor\nicons/forms/rules" as Admin
component "API Gateway / BFF\nTaxonomy API facade" as BFF
component "TaxonomyController\nDynamicEnvironmentController\nAdminTaxonomyController" as Controller
component "Taxonomy Use Cases\nResolveCategoryTree\nPublishTaxonomy\nMapRequestCategory\nConfigureDynamicEnvironment" as UseCases
component "Taxonomy Policies\nversion compatibility\ncategory visibility\nform validation\nmigration mapping" as Policies
component "Ports\nTaxonomyRepo\nLocalizationPort\nSearchIndexPort\nAnalyticsPort\nOutboxPort" as Ports
database "PostgreSQL\ncategory\ntag\ncategory_rule\nform_schema\nversion" as DB
component "localization-service\nlabels\nslugs\nicons metadata" as Loc
component "search-service\nfacets\nfilters\nmatching projection" as Search
component "analytics/AI\nno-result quality\ncategory suggestion" as Analytics
queue "Kafka / Outbox\nTaxonomyPublished\nCategoryRuleChanged\nDynamicEnvUpdated" as Kafka

Client --> BFF : HTTPS
Admin --> BFF : HTTPS admin
BFF --> Controller : REST
Controller --> UseCases : command/query
UseCases --> Policies : validate
Policies --> Ports : ports
Ports --> DB : persist/read
Ports --> Loc : localized labels
Ports --> Search : facets/index
UseCases --> Analytics : quality/suggestions
UseCases --> Kafka : events

note bottom
Taxonomy service owns canonical category/tag/rule/form-schema model.
Search, localization and clients consume published taxonomy versions.
end note
@enduml
